   <!--
<DIV STYLE="border: 3px double darkred; margin-top: 10; margin-right: 55; margin-bottom: 15; margin-left: 66; background-color: #D4E6FF; padding-top: 15px; padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 10px; text-align: left;">
  <p align="left">Dear Readers:   
  <p> With great sadness, we announce the passing of this site&rsquo;s founder, Dr. Charles Darling. Charles was completely devoted to Capital Community College, where he joyfully worked for 35 years as an English professor and, briefly, as Director of Public Relations. </p>
  <p>Charles developed The Guide to Grammar and Writing in 1996, originally to help his students write reports and research papers. In addition, he wanted to create a place where students could look up grammatical issues for themselves. The Guide to Grammar and Writing rapidly took on a life of its own, mushrooming into a wildly popular site, with upwards of 30,000 hits per day from all over the world. It was a labor of love for Charles and, when he retired in 2005, he continued working on it. </p>
  <p>Charles thought it was essential that the site remain a free service, but laughed at the implications if it were otherwise. </p>
  <p>&ldquo;If I collected a dime for every e-mail, I wouldn&rsquo;t have to do the painting of my doors and walls myself in our remodeled home,&rdquo; Charles told reporter Bob Sudyk (The Hartford Courant, Northeast magazine, 4/11/04). </p>
  <p>Charles Darling was one special human being. He was kind, smart and funny, with an abundance of love that he showered upon his wife, sons, grandsons, and his Capital Community College students and colleagues. He will be deeply missed. </p>
  <p>- John McNamara<br>
    <font size="2">Director of Institutional Advancement <strong><br>
    The Capital Community College Foundation</strong> <br>
    950 Main Street, Hartford, CT 06103</font></p>
  <p align="center" class="style3">The college is establishing a fund in memory of Dr. Darling. <br>
    For those who wish to donate online, please click the link below.</p>
